Series XI: Archived Websites, September 2007-ongoing

Extent

4 websites in 4 archived websites.

Scope and Content Note

District Council 37 (DC 37) is a local union of the American Federation of State, County, and Municipal Employees (AFSCME) which represents New York City public employees and employees in the healthcare industry. DC 37 was founded in 1944. The website contains information on locals, contracts and agreements, news listings, press releases, their newsletter, Public Employee Press, their political action campaign, blog, and member benefits and services.

Also includes the website created by DC 37 to update members on information related to the COVID-19 pandemic. The website contains worksite updates and reopening plans, resources for members, government benefits, and related news.

Accruals

New site crawls are accrued semiannually.

Appraisal

Crawl was limited to domains and subdomains of http://www.dc37.net/, https://dc37blog.wordpress.com/, https://www.dc37covid19.net/, and http://www.dc37pep.net/ in order to remain within the collection scope and data constraints.

Physical Characteristics and Technical Requirements

Due to technical or privacy issues, archived websites may not be exact copies of the original website at the time of the web crawl. Certain file types will not be captured dependent on how they are embedded in the site. Other parts of websites that the crawler has difficulty capturing includes Javascript, streaming content, database-driven content, and highly interactive content. Full-Text searches of archived websites are available at https://archive-it.org/organizations/567.
